The paper discusses a matchmaking framework for online player-versus-player games that maximizes player engagement. This involves optimizing various factors such as player skill, playstyle, and preferences. This falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) since the proposed framework involves using algorithms to optimize matchmaking. The paper also mentions the use of player data and simulation, which could fall under the categories of social and information sciences (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
